Ecofeminism and environmental justice: Examining the intersection of gender, race, and environmental activism
Fatima Begum
This paper has demonstrated how ecofeminism provides a powerful lens for understanding the intersection of gender, race, and environmental activism. By exploring case studies, of women of color and indigenous women at the forefront of environmental justice movements, we have seen how ecofeminism challenges environmental degradation and social oppression simultaneously. Women, particularly those from marginalized communities, are essential to the success of environmental justice movements, and their activism is reshaping global environmental policies. 
